In this proclamation, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. reflects on the challenges facing the United States, including the pandemic, economic crisis, racial injustice, climate crisis, and political extremism. Despite these challenges, he emphasizes that democracy has prevailed and calls for unity as the key to overcoming these obstacles. President Biden expresses his commitment to saving lives, rebuilding the economy, addressing systemic racism, and confronting the climate crisis. He believes that unity will not only protect democracy but also allow the United States to lead by example. The President prays for strength and asks all Americans to join him in the cause of democracy, hoping that it will unite the nation. He declares January 20, 2021, a National Day of Unity and encourages the people to come together and write the next chapter of American democracy.